videos.description: Marshall's Hyleck Foster raises his arm slightly before receiving a punt that he returns for a touchdown, but the motion is ruled an invalid fair catch signal.
videos.headline: Fair catch or just keeping balance?

videos.description: Marshall's Chase Litton takes a shot downfield into double coverage, but Colorado State's Jordan Fogal makes the pick.
videos.headline: Colorado State intercepts Litton's pass into double coverage

videos.description: Marshall strikes first on a Tyre Brady catch-and-run that puts the Thundering Herd up 7-0.
videos.headline: Brady burns defender for 76-yard Marshall TD

videos.description: Colorado State's Detrich Clark beats his defender to the pylon to tie Marshall 7-7 in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Colorado State caps 15-play drive with Clark TD

videos.description: Ryan Yuracheck puts the Thundering Herd up 14-7 after coming down with a 15-yard Chase Litton touchdown pass in traffic.
videos.headline: Yurachek splits double-team for Marshall TD

videos.description: Colorado State QB Nick Stevens runs up the middle for a 9-yard score to tie Marshall at 14.
videos.headline: Colorado State ties game on QB draw

videos.description: Marshall's Keion Davis takes the handoff and shows a combination of speed and power on his way to end zone on a 68-yard run.
videos.headline: Davis rumbles 68 yards for memorable TD

videos.description: Colorado State head coach Mike Bobo says that his defense has struggled stopping Marshall's explosive plays, and that his offense needs to make some of their own in the second half.
videos.headline: Colorado State to limit Marshall's explosive plays in 2nd half

videos.description: Tyler King leaves the Colorado State defense in the dust with a nice juke and insane speed as Marshall leads Colorado State 28-14.
videos.headline: King turns on burners for 90-yard Marshall TD run

videos.description: Colorado State quarterback Nick Stevens drops back and slings a beautiful ball to Detrich Clark to cut the deficit to 31-21 in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Colorado State cuts deficit on TD strike

videos.description: Colorado State's Anthony Hawkins intercepts Chase Litton's pass to give the Rams the ball back down 10 points in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Hawkins interception keeps Colorado State in striking distance

videos.description: It appeared that Michael Gallup remarkably got a foot in bounds on the touchdown catch, but the officials overturned the Colorado State score.
videos.headline: Colorado State TD reversed after review

videos.description: Dalyn Dawkins takes the snap and sneaks in from one yard out to make the score 31-28 in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Colorado State punches it in on QB sneak

videos.description: Colorado State's Michael Gallup only needs one hand to haul in a third-down pass to extend a drive late in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Gallup keeps drive alive with OBJ-like snag

videos.description: Colorado State QB Nick Stevens catches his own batted pass, but does not gain enough yards for a first down.
videos.headline: Marshall bats pass to stop Colorado State's drive
